question: The "Lene Hara Cave" is located in which country?
explanation: The Lene Hara Cave is located in the island country of Timor-Leste or East Timor in the Lesser Sunda Islands of Malay Archipelago. This main caves system has provided evidence that Timor Island has been occupied by humans since at least 35000 years and humans crossed the waters of Wallacea between the Pleistocene continents of Sunda and Sahul. Holocene fish hooks made from shell and shell beads and hand stencils were discovered from these caves.
